  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But before that, my brother, George-- who prior to the war, before the war, had plans to go to America.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But during that-- at the time before the war, he was about to get a visa to-- to go to America.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But because of the influx of refugees from Germany, Germany expelled all the so-called Polish citizens, the Jewish citizens, back to Poland.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so they set back his visa to give them priority, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the Polish Jews from Germany.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] But he had some documents, some papers, that showed that he was on a waiting list.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so he tried to get a visa.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He couldn't get a visa.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But he found out that in Lithuania, in-- in Wilno, there was a Polish-- not the Polish, the American Embassy [INAUDIBLE] still had an office there.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So he went to-- to Wilno, which is-- was also occupied by the Russians.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he was able to get there.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
